<p id="d1e5330">In this Section we model the imposition of non-pharmaceutical interventions (NPIs) by replacing the constant value 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5333" display="inline" altimg="si49.svg">
   <msub>
    <mrow>
     <mi>β</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mn>0</mn>
    </mrow>
   </msub>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> in Eq. 
 <xref rid="fd1j" ref-type="disp-formula">(1j)</xref> with a piecewise-constant function denoted by 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5348" display="inline" altimg="si112.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>β</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. We solve the equations from the initial time 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5362" display="inline" altimg="si67.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">=</mo>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">−</mo>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">o</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">f</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">f</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">s</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">e</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> (initial conditions 
 <xref rid="fd4" ref-type="disp-formula">(4)</xref>) out to a fixed final time 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5393" display="inline" altimg="si114.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">=</mo>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">T</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. Specifically, we take: 
 <disp-formula id="fd9a">
  <label>(9a)</label>
  <math id="d1e5409" display="block" altimg="si115.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>β</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">=</mo>
    <mfenced open="{">
     <mrow>
      <mtable align="axis" equalrows="false" columnlines="none" equalcolumns="false" class="array">
       <mtr>
        <mtd class="array" columnalign="left">
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi>β</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>,</mo>
         <mspace width="2em"/>
         <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
         <mo>∈</mo>
         <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mo>−</mo>
          <msub>
           <mrow>
            <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
           </mrow>
           <mrow>
            <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">o</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">f</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">f</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">s</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">e</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
           </mrow>
          </msub>
          <mo>,</mo>
          <msub>
           <mrow>
            <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
           </mrow>
           <mrow>
            <mn>0</mn>
           </mrow>
          </msub>
          <mo>]</mo>
         </mrow>
         <mo>,</mo>
         <mspace width="1em"/>
        </mtd>
       </mtr>
       <mtr>
        <mtd class="array" columnalign="left">
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi>β</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mfenced open="[" close="]">
          <mrow>
           <mn>1</mn>
           <mo>−</mo>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
           <mrow>
            <mo>(</mo>
            <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
            <mo>)</mo>
           </mrow>
          </mrow>
         </mfenced>
         <mo>,</mo>
         <mspace width="2em"/>
         <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
         <mo>∈</mo>
         <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <msub>
           <mrow>
            <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
           </mrow>
           <mrow>
            <mn>0</mn>
           </mrow>
          </msub>
          <mo>,</mo>
          <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">T</mi>
          <mo>]</mo>
         </mrow>
         <mo>.</mo>
         <mspace width="1em"/>
        </mtd>
       </mtr>
      </mtable>
     </mrow>
    </mfenced>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>Here, 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5530" display="inline" altimg="si118.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is a second piecewise-constant functions. In this way, the model 
 <xref rid="fd1j" ref-type="disp-formula">(1j)</xref> is solved with no controls for 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5547" display="inline" altimg="si119.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">≤</mo>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mn>0</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>; controls are introduced at time 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5562" display="inline" altimg="si120.svg">
   <msub>
    <mrow>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mn>0</mn>
    </mrow>
   </msub>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. The time 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5573" display="inline" altimg="si120.svg">
   <msub>
    <mrow>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mn>0</mn>
    </mrow>
   </msub>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is fixed. For consistency, the following bounds apply to 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5583" display="inline" altimg="si118.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>: 
 <disp-formula id="fd9b">
  <label>(9b)</label>
  <math id="d1e5602" display="block" altimg="si123.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mn>0</mn>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">≤</mo>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">≤</mo>
    <mn>1</mn>
    <mo>,</mo>
    <mspace width="2em"/>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">∈</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mo>[</mo>
     <msub>
      <mrow>
       <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mn>0</mn>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">T</mi>
     <mo>]</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo>.</mo>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> The piecewise-constant function 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5649" display="inline" altimg="si118.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is characterized as follows: 
 <disp-formula id="fd10">
  <label>(10)</label>
  <math id="d1e5669" display="block" altimg="si125.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo>(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     <mo>)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">=</mo>
    <mfenced open="{">
     <mrow>
      <mtable align="axis" equalrows="false" columnlines="none" equalcolumns="false" class="array">
       <mtr>
        <mtd class="array" columnalign="left">
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>,</mo>
         <mspace width="1em"/>
        </mtd>
        <mtd class="array" columnalign="left">
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>&lt;</mo>
         <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
         <mo>≤</mo>
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">s</mi>
           <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>,</mo>
        </mtd>
       </mtr>
       <mtr>
        <mtd class="array" columnalign="left">
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>,</mo>
         <mspace width="1em"/>
        </mtd>
        <mtd class="array" columnalign="left">
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">s</mi>
           <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>&lt;</mo>
         <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
         <mo>≤</mo>
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">s</mi>
           <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>,</mo>
        </mtd>
       </mtr>
       <mtr>
        <mtd class="array" columnalign="left">
         <mo>⋮</mo>
         <mspace width="1em"/>
        </mtd>
        <mtd class="array" columnalign="left">
         <div class="mphantom" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
          <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur" xmlns="">a</mi>
         </div>
        </mtd>
       </mtr>
       <mtr>
        <mtd class="array" columnalign="left">
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">n</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>,</mo>
         <mspace width="1em"/>
        </mtd>
        <mtd class="array" columnalign="left">
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">s</mi>
           <mo>,</mo>
           <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">n</mi>
           <mo linebreak="badbreak">−</mo>
           <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo>&lt;</mo>
         <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
         <mo>≤</mo>
         <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">T</mi>
         <mo>.</mo>
        </mtd>
       </mtr>
      </mtable>
     </mrow>
    </mfenced>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>Here, 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5810" display="inline" altimg="si311.svg">
   <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">n</mi>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is an integer (one or greater), 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5815" display="inline" altimg="si131.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mn>1</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo>,</mo>
    <mo>…</mo>
    <mo>,</mo>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">u</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">n</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> are real numbers between zero and one, and 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5839" display="inline" altimg="si132.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">s</mi>
      <mn>1</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo>,</mo>
    <mo>…</mo>
    <mo>,</mo>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">s</mi>
      <mo>,</mo>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">n</mi>
      <mo>−</mo>
      <mn>1</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> are switching times (real numbers between 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5874" display="inline" altimg="si120.svg">
   <msub>
    <mrow>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mn>0</mn>
    </mrow>
   </msub>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5884" display="inline" altimg="si134.svg">
   <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">T</mi>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, such that 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="d1e5889" display="inline" altimg="si135.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">s</mi>
      <mn>1</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">&lt;</mo>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">⋯</mo>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">t</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">s</mi>
      <mo>,</mo>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">n</mi>
      <mo>−</mo>
      <mn>1</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">&lt;</mo>
    <mi mathvariant="bold-fraktur">T</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>). In practice, the switching times correspond to how often the NPIs are updated.
</p>
